│ add vp<%5>, vp<%1>\n      REPLICATE ir<%gep.dst> = getelementptr ir<%dst>, ir<%iv.next>\n  │
│ REPLICATE store ir<0>, ir<%gep.dst>\n    ```\n    - `vp<%1>` represents the uniform step   │
│ value (`%step`, which is 2).\n    - `vp<%5>` is a `SCALAR-STEPS` VPValue, representing the │
│ per-lane scalar values of the primary induction variable (`%iv`).\n    - The `REPLICATE`   │
│ recipe for `ir<%iv.next>` is the key. It instructs the vectorizer to generate a scalar     │
